        <h1>LeetCode 154: Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array II (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Suppose an array of length n sorted in ascending order is rotated between 1 and n times. This array may
                contain duplicates. For example, the array [1,3] rotated any number of times could be [3,1]. Find the
                minimum element of this array. You must write an algorithm that runs in O(log n) time in the average
                case.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,3]<br>
                Output: 1<br>
                Explanation: The minimum element is 1.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int findMin(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        int lo = 0, hi = nums.size() - 1;
        while (lo &lt; hi) {
            // Current range already sorted
            if (nums[lo] &lt; nums[hi])
                return nums[lo];
            int mid = lo + (hi - lo) / 2;
            if (nums[mid] &gt; nums[hi]) {
                lo = mid + 1;
            }
            else if (nums[mid] &lt; nums[hi]) {
                hi = mid;
            }
            else {
                hi--; // skip duplicate safely
            }
        }
        return nums[lo];
    }
};</code></pre>
